Real-Time Analytics 

You are working on a real-time analytics system that processes a continuous stream of data. The data comes in the form of an array of integers, and you need to calculate the maximum value within a sliding window of size k. As the window moves from left to right, the system needs to efficiently update the maximum value.



You are given an integer array nums[] and an integer k, and your task is to return the maximum values in each sliding window of size k as the window slides from left to right.

Input format :
First line contains an integer n — the number of elements in the array
Second line contains n space-separated integers representing the array nums[]
Third line contains an integer k — the size of the sliding window
Output format :
Print the result in the format:
Maximum values in each sliding window: v1 v2 v3 ... Where v1 v2 v3 ... are the maximum values of each

sliding window position separated by spaces

Code constraints :
1 <= k <= nums.length <= 10^5

-10^4 <= nums[i] <= 10^4





Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
4
3 1 4 5
2
Output 1 :
Maximum values in each sliding window: 3 4 5 
Input 2 :
5
1 3 2 5 4
1
Output 2 :
Maximum values in each sliding window: 1 3 2 5 4


So;ution:


// You are using GCC
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

void cal(vector<int> &nums,int k){
    int n = nums.size();
    
    
    vector<int>ans;
    
    int MaxEle = INT_MIN;
    
    for(int i=0;i<n-k+1;i++){
        
        for(int j=i;j<i+k;j++){
            
            MaxEle = max(MaxEle,nums[j]);
            
        }
        
        ans.push_back(MaxEle);
        MaxEle = INT_MIN;
    }
    
    for(int i:ans){
        cout<<i<<" ";
    }
    
    
}

int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    vector<int>arr(n);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        cin>>arr[i];
    }
    
    int k;
    cin>>k;
    
    cout<<"Maximum values in each sliding window: ";
    cal(arr,k);
}
